Bambusa nutans

    Authority   Wall.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3623

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   An evergreen or deciduous bamboo with fairly thick-walled culms
   reaching a height of 10-14 m.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial bamboo. (GMIN estimated by the compiler).
   COMMON NAMES
   Bamboo nutans.
   FURTHER INF
   Bamboo nutans can be found up to 1600 m in elevation. Bamboos grow
   between the latitudes 40°N and S. Though the big bamboo forests usually
   occur between 15-25°N and S.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Hassan M 1988 pp 505-513 [RAIN, TEMP, SAL, DRA, TEXT, PH, DEP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 417 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 8 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Troup R 1921 pp 1001-1002 [USE]

